<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Given the following classes:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class A
{
    public $test;
 
    public function setTest($test)
    {
        $this-&gt;test = $test;
        return $this;
    }
}

class B extends A
{
}
</code></pre>

<p>If you configure DI to inject class A's 'test parameter with the string 'a' and class B's 'test' parameter with the string 'b', and you do $b = $di-&gt;get('B'); you will get an instance of B with the test parameter set to the string 'a', which is clearly not the expected result.</p>

<p>I have wrote a failing test to illustrate the issue: <a href="https://github.com/EvanDotPro/zf2/compare/hotfix/di-parent-parameters">https://github.com/EvanDotPro/zf2/â€¦</a></p>

<p>This test actually used to pass at one point, and some change broke this behavior. If I can figure out when that happened, I'll update this issue.</p>

